{
  "texts": [
    "Other works study and present innovative ways and improvements to existing ER methods applied to complex real-world problems and are identified with a purple mark in Fig. 1.",
    "These markings are at the inferior right corner of each box that delimits an article and its authors.",
    "The second distinction criterion concerns the strategies of ER each work is approaching, identified by the larger label blocks in the chart vertically, from top to bottom (e.g., naive or non-naive ER?",
    "What form of prioritization or relevance does it focus on?).",
    "Lastly, the third criterion is the algorithm modifications or architectural changes that each work proposes and uses (e.g., a new neural network architecture, new exploration strategies, or new data structures for the memory of the experience)."
  ]
}